3. (Optional) Handle false-positive surface: add `overrides` blocks in `factory.js` / preset files for legitimate exemptions (`schema.ts`, `*.test.*`, `**/test-utils/**`, `**/scripts/**`).\n\n4. **Rule patterns** — mini-recipes:\n   - **Pure-AST rule** (e.g., `no-error-status-response`) — match a `CallExpression` / `NewExpression` shape and report.\n   - **Cross-file rule** (e.g., `no-deprecated-feature-flag-references`) — read repo state, cache by monorepo root, walk up via `package.json` workspaces field. Show the `findMonorepoRoot` + cache pattern.\n   - **Filename-aware rule** (e.g., `filename-match-export`) — use `context.getFilename()` and `path.basename`.\n   - **Package-aware rule** (e.g., `no-self-package-import`) — find nearest `package.json`, cache lookups.\n\n5. **Don'ts**:\n   - Don’t inline `messages` strings at the `context.report` site — always use `messageId` so tests stay decoupled from copy.\n   - Don’t turn on autofix if it conflicts with other rules (e.g., `factory/types-file-organization`). Document this in the rule header, mirroring the `no-self-package-import` comment.\n   - Don’t skip the test file. Every existing rule has one; rule unit tests run in CI.\n   - Don’t forget both `factory.js` AND `plugin.js` wiring — they are independent.\n   - Don’t use `npm run lint --filter=…` (no `--`) — npm eats the flag and turbo runs everything (~9 GB RAM).\n\n6. **Off-by-default rollout pattern** — copy the precedent of `no-direct-process-env`/`no-unsafe-json-parse`/`no-error-status-response`: ship as `'off'` in the base preset, enable in target app’s `.eslintrc.js`, then migrate other apps one at a time.\n\n## Templates\n\n- **`templates/rule.js.md`** — full skeleton with `'use strict'`, JSDoc header, `meta` block, `messages`, `schema: []`, `create(context)` returning visitor functions, optional helpers, optional `module.exports._internal` for testability.\n\n- **`templates/rule.test.js.md`** — `RuleTester` setup with `@typescript-eslint/parser`, ES2020 module sourceType, valid + invalid blocks using `messageId`, `output: null` for non-fixable rules, fixture-filename pattern when the rule needs a `package.json` upstream.\n\n## checklists.md\n\nA pre-merge checklist that captures:\n- [ ] Rule has unit tests with at least one valid and one invalid case per branch\n- [ ] Registered in `rules/index.js`\n- [ ] Wired into `factory.js` AND `plugin.js`\n- [ ] Decided on-by-default vs migration (documented why)\n- [ ] All affected packages: lint clean, typecheck clean, test green\n- [ ] Knip clean\n- [ ] Any `eslint-disable` carries a `--` justification and a codeowner is on the PR\n- [ ] PR title follows Conventional Commits (`feat(eslint-config): add <rule-name> rule`)\n\n## Workflow diagram (in SKILL.md)\n\n```mermaid\nflowchart TD\n  A[Decide convention] --> B[Scaffold rule.js + test.js]\n  B --> C[Register in rules/index.js]\n  C --> D[Wire into factory.js + plugin.js]\n  D --> E{Violation count?}\n  E -->|Small| F[Ship as error everywhere]\n  E -->|Large| G[Off in preset + on in target app]\n  F --> H[Sweep & fix violations]\n  G --> H\n  H --> I[Verify lint/types/tests/knip]\n  I --> J[Open PR]\n```\n\n## How this handles the edge cases I found\n\n- **Cross-file state / monorepo-root walk** → covered in “Rule patterns” section with the cache pattern from `no-deprecated-feature-flag-references`.\n- **Codeowner-gated disables** → explicit “Don’ts” bullet referencing CI commit #13331.\n- **`--filter` foot-gun** → called out explicitly with the `--` placement, citing AGENTS.md.\n- **Test fixture packages** → reference the `test-files/self-import-pkg/` precedent and when to use it.\n- **Off-by-default migration** → dedicated section with concrete precedents.\n- **Autofix conflict with sibling rules** → “Don’ts” bullet with `no-self-package-import` precedent.\n\nAfter creation I’ll suggest: run `/skills` to confirm it’s listed, then invoke it on a real new-rule task to validate.\n",
