            "plan": "\n# Skill Plan: `create-lint-rule`\n\n## Location\n**Project skill**: `.factory/skills/create-lint-rule/`\nRepo-specific to factory-mono's `packages/eslint-config/` plugin; shareable with teammates via git.\n\n## Why a skill\n44 rules added to `packages/eslint-config/rules/` over time, all following the same pattern (rule + test + index registration + preset wiring + monorepo-wide sweep). New contributors keep rediscovering the conventions, the `--`-before-`--filter` foot-gun, the codeowner-gated `eslint-disable` policy, and the right rollout shape. This skill encodes the workflow with a strict TDD spine and a hard quality bar.\n\n## Skill directory contents\n\n```\n.factory/skills/create-lint-rule/\n├── SKILL.md\n├── templates/\n│   ├── rule.js.md          # rule scaffold (meta, schema, create())\n│   └── rule.test.js.md     # RuleTester scaffold (valid/invalid blocks)\n├── checklists.md           # pre-merge checklist\n└── references.md           # exemplar rules + exemplar PR descriptions\n```\n\nTemplates as `.md` (markdown with fenced code) match the convention used in `process-env-migration/templates/*.ts.md`.\n\n## SKILL.md frontmatter\n\n```yaml\n---\nname: create-lint-rule\ndescription: >\n  Author a new custom ESLint rule in @factory/eslint-config using a strict\n  TDD workflow, sweep the entire monorepo to fix every violation, and ship\n  it as a PR. Use when you need to enforce a new code-quality convention\n  via lint. Not for fixing violations of existing rules — use the dedicated\n  ban-type-assertions / process-env-migration / no-use-effect /\n  fix-knip-unused-exports skills instead.\n---\n```\n\n## SKILL.md body — the 6-step workflow (this is the spine)\n\n### Step 1. Define motivating examples as tests, verbatim from the ticket\n\nBefore writing a single line of rule code, translate the ticket's BAD/GOOD examples into `RuleTester` cases.\n\n- Create `packages/eslint-config/rules/<name>.test.js` from `templates/rule.test.js.md`