ollows Conventional Commits\n- [ ] PR description follows Step-6 template (motivation, hazard, skips, verification, test count, edge cases, ticket)\n\n## references.md\n\n- **Exemplar rules** (with one-line description of why each is exemplary):\n  - `rules/no-shell-injection.js` — clean AST-only rule with strong test coverage.\n  - `rules/no-deprecated-feature-flag-references.js` — cross-file state, monorepo-root walk, cache.\n  - `rules/no-self-package-import.js` — package-aware rule, intentionally not autofixable, documents why in header.\n  - `rules/filename-match-export.js` — filename-aware rule.\n  - `rules/no-error-status-response.js` — conservative matching, documents trade-offs.\n- **Exemplar PR descriptions** (links + the structural elements they demonstrate):\n  - PR #13116 — motivation + concrete prod regression + workspace-by-workspace verification.\n  - PR #10770 — test count stat + edge cases handled in commit follow-up.\n  - PR #12509 (`no-self-package-import`) — large sweep with rule + 50 file fixes.\n\n## Workflow diagram\n\n```mermaid\nflowchart TD\n  T[Ticket BAD/GOOD examples] --> S1[Step1: test cases verbatim]\n  S1 --> S2[Step2: implement rule]\n  S2 --> R{All Step1 tests pass?}\n  R -->|no| S2\n  R -->|yes| S3[Step3: sweep + triage]\n  S3 --> Q{< 10% FP disables AND <= 12 total?}\n  Q -->|no| S2\n  Q -->|yes| S5[Step5: create-pr]\n  S5 --> S6[Step6: PR desc per exemplars]\n```\n\n## How this addresses the edge cases I found\n\n- **Codeowner-gated disables (#13331)** — explicit budget cap (≤ 12) and required `--` justification.\n- **`--filter` foot-gun (AGENTS.md)** — called out in every command snippet.\n- **Cross-file state** — template includes the `findMonorepoRoot` + cache pattern, exemplar rules reference it.\n- **Off-by-default migration** — Step 2 has a decision branch with concrete precedents.\n- **Autofix conflicts with sibling rules** — Don'ts call out the `no-self-package-import` precedent of intentionally omitting autofix.\n- **Te