oring, after architecture changes, or for security audits.\ncommit-security-scan: Analyze code changes for security vulnerabilities using LLM reasoning and threat model patterns. Use for PR reviews, pre-commit checks, or branch comparisons.\nvulnerability-validation: Validate security findings from commit-security-scan by assessing exploitability, filtering false positives, and generating proof-of-concept exploits. Use after running commit-security-scan to confirm vulnerabilities.\nstatsig-ops: Inspect and update Statsig gates and dynamic configs with Siggy for factory-mono. Use when auditing rollout state, validating live Statsig values, or making approved Statsig changes.\naws-sso-user-provisioner: Add users to AWS SSO with a specified role. Use when asked to grant AWS SSO access, add someone to AWS, or give AWS permissions to a team member.\norg-migration: Write, test, and run Firestore organization document migrations using the apps/scripts migration framework. Use when backfilling fields on org docs, migrating data between collections, or running bulk updates across all organizations.\ncreate-lint-rule: Author a new custom ESLint rule in @factory/eslint-config using a strict TDD workflow, sweep the entire monorepo to fix every violation as a guaranteed NOOP, and ship it as a PR. Use when you need to enforce a new code-quality convention via lint. Not for fixing violations of existing rules -- use ban-type-assertions, process-env-migration, no-use-effect, or fix-knip-unused-exports instead.\nclean-feature-flags: Audit and retire entries in `packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts` against live Statsig state. Use when sweeping launched/abandoned flags, draining the registry, or producing a per-flag cleanup PR with surgical, hermetic commits.\nautomated-qa-prod: Automated QA testing for the Factory web app PROD/PREPROD environments. Use when you want to run a smoke test of the preprod or production environment. For dev environment QA, use the automated-qa-d