ites.\n- The \"fix\" is \"use the bounded/explicit alternative\" rather than \"do the same thing more safely.\"\n\nIf the classification is unclear, **default to correctness rule** and tighten scope until <=12 disables is realistic. If you can't get below 12 even after scope narrowing, the rule is a deprecation rule -- flip the gate.",
